cx.corp.lacuna.core.domain

Interface NativeProcess

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NativeProcessImpl

    public interface NativeProcess
    Represents a native process running on the host computer.

    This model object contains the process id, owner name and description of the represented process.

    See Also:
    NativeProcessEnumerator, NativeProcessCollector

      • getDescription

        java.lang.String getDescription()
        Gets the description of the process.

        On Linux platforms, this value is the command line of the running process, whereas on Windows platforms this value is the image name of the process's executable.

        If the process cannot be accessed, this value may be null or empty.

        Returns:
        The description of the process, or UNKNOWN_DESCRIPTION if the description is unknown.

      • setDescription

        void setDescription(java.lang.String desc)

      • getOwner

        java.lang.String getOwner()
        Gets the owner of the process.

        If the process cannot be accessed, this value may be null or empty.

        Returns:
        The owner of the process, or UNKNOWN_OWNER if the owner is unknown.

      • setOwner
